Key Match Events: Jude Bellingham scored a late bicycle kick to equalize the game in the 95th minute.
Harry Kane headed in an extra-time winner to secure the victory for England.
Ivan Schranz scored an early goal for Slovakia in the 25th minute.
The game went into extra time after Bellingham's equalizer.
Post-Match Reflections: England's manager praised the team's resilience after coming back from a 1-0 deficit.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at VELTINS-Arena in Gelsenkirchen, Germany.
